<subSubSection id="3A8BD2AEC77511E675FCD6176E92C995" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="5D309FD0A3B7A633D5D968EE73E3F4AB" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C48F74C724121502F3EE6E17B5714923" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">
This species belongs to the 
<emphasis id="220F6D1F14383D750791029DF15DDFCD" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">miniatus</emphasis>
species group (
<taxonomicName id="9D02C77E2FBC50589F37C2A895CEF4AD" genus="S." lsidName="S. creticus" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" rank="species" species="creticus">
<emphasis id="6BB4B9145C7544F2992BC44A8A67D796" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">S. creticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Warncke, 1992, 
<taxonomicName id="4CEDB38954AAE204C75AD71FEF86F0F9" genus="S." lsidName="S. haladai" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" rank="species" species="haladai">
<emphasis id="1BDCEF66B353B829F7A55FAAC8E97ADF" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">S. haladai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Warncke, 1992, 
<taxonomicName id="339D717CAF0DA50712E0C978C8098D90" genus="S." lsidName="S. larochei" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" rank="species" species="larochei">
<emphasis id="5DCB755F4E9E2821655E9E13B270F046" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">S. larochei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Warncke, 1992, 
<taxonomicName id="89065E0F819E9F798C95294287148D59" genus="S." lsidName="S. marginatus" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" rank="species" species="marginatus">
<emphasis id="2BE89A2C4BF4B79050C734A19FB10DBA" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">S. marginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hagens, 1882, 
<taxonomicName id="0EA2C53F3C4D425F9FD63A315B548168" genus="S." lsidName="S. miniatus" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" rank="species" species="miniatus">
<emphasis id="02375B42A2D05ABCBAF0CA2FD3A8BA4F" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">S. miniatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hagens, 1882, 
<taxonomicName id="70B4976DF45AB5580BF3A0D8E198E549" genus="S." lsidName="S. nomioidis" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" rank="species" species="nomioidis">
<emphasis id="A15C3835345F3FDDE8AFEED176913347" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">S. nomioidis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Pesenko, 1979, 
<taxonomicName id="7089B3714D653F463091F4614D01284C" genus="S." lsidName="S. schawrzi" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" rank="species" species="schawrzi">
<emphasis id="7A9CFB9A2C50B4914CBB584CF1D79E1C" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">S. schawrzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Astafurova &amp; Proshchalykin, 2014, and 
<taxonomicName id="57BB45BD537F4BF8330EB548903723CC" genus="S." lsidName="S. sandykachis" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" rank="species" species="sandykachis">
<emphasis id="44E5F8DB32A8083D2AD5E3902D066789" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">S. sandykachis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Astafurova &amp; Proshchalykin, 2018), with the same length and transverse F1-F3 in females. Among species of this group 
<taxonomicName id="3474BC6EC63B8ED67CDD2916079A7E7D" genus="S." lsidName="S. marginatus" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" rank="species" species="marginatus">
<emphasis id="3AC63F12EE93EB7B73E5DB332BBCEF96" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">S. marginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most close to 
<taxonomicName id="5EAFD06C54C4C28612F19B1B24747CAF" genus="S." lsidName="S. miniatus" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" rank="species" species="miniatus">
<emphasis id="817A40E35A35CC865B1E02ED8C9F02A0" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">S. miniatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C67723824AEB859C46178227992ABDA1" genus="S." lsidName="S. nomioidis" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" rank="species" species="nomioidis">
<emphasis id="38E57159677FB09F241EE80C69489F65" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">S. nomioidis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as they have a similar sculpture and structure of the body. Hence females of the three species are challenging to distinguish, but the male differs from the other two species by smaller triangular gonostylus. Differences between these three species are outlined by 
<bibRefCitation id="B49855BB75FC0A7BAA14F6F7173F8A0D" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3311.1.1" author="Bogusch, P" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="22" pageNumber="35" pagination="1 - 41" refId="B20" refString="Bogusch, P, Straka, J, 2012. Review and identification of the cuckoo bees of central Europe (Hymenoptera: Halictidae: Sphecodes). . Zootaxa 3311: 1 - 41" title="Review and identification of the cuckoo bees of central Europe (Hymenoptera: Halictidae: Sphecodes)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3311.1.1" volume="3311" year="2012">Bogusch and Straka (2012)</bibRefCitation>
and between females of this species group by 
<bibRefCitation id="8B30F3772F3AD4403C5C0B43866F65C3" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4441.1.4" author="Astafurova, YuV" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="22" pageNumber="35" pagination="76 - 88" refId="B16" refString="Astafurova, YuV, Proshchalykin, MYu, Schwarz, M, 2018c. New and little known bees of the genus Sphecodes Latreille, 1804 (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Halictidae) from Central Asia. . Zootaxa 4441: 76 - 88" title="New and little known bees of the genus Sphecodes Latreille, 1804 (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Halictidae) from Central Asia." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4441.1.4" volume="4441" year="2018 c">Astafurova et al. (2018c)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
